  "prompt": "Which is the best smartphone under \u20b912,000?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, the smartphone market is quite dynamic, and several options are available under \u20b912,000 that offer good performance and features. While the best choice can vary based on personal preferences and needs, here are a few popular options that have been well-received around that price point:\n\n1. **Realme Narzo 50**:\n   - Display: 6.6-inch FHD+ with high refresh rate\n   - Processor: MediaTek Helio G96\n   - Camera: Triple rear camera setup\n   - Battery: 5000mAh with fast charging\n\n2. **Xiaomi Redmi 10**:\n   - Display: 6.67-inch FHD+ DotDisplay\n   - Processor: MediaTek Helio G88\n   - Camera: Dual rear cameras\n   - Battery: 5000mAh\n\n3. **Samsung Galaxy M13**:\n   - Display: 6.6-inch FHD+ LCD\n   - Processor: Exynos 850\n   - Camera: Triple rear camera setup\n   - Battery: 6000mAh\n\n4. **Poco M4 Pro**:\n   - Display: 6.43-inch FHD+ AMOLED\n   - Processor: MediaTek Dimensity 810\n   - Camera: 64MP triple camera setup\n   - Battery: 5000mAh\n\n5. **Moto G31**:\n   - Display: 6.4-inch FHD+ AMOLED\n   - Processor: MediaTek Helio G85\n   - Camera: Triple camera system\n   - Battery: 5000mAh\n\nI recommend checking the latest reviews and comparisons to see which models are currently available and suited to your preferences. Prices may fluctuate, and new models may have been introduced since my last update, so it\u2019s a good idea to visit your local electronics store or an online retail platform for the most current data.",
